Here's the wider map so you can see where the gaps actually are: Yoodli is the data-driven pick with the most detailed analytics dashboard, Orai is structure-driven with step-by-step lesson progression, Speeko is anxiety-driven with a calm, meditation-style approach, Toastmasters is community-driven with real live audiences. Poised does live desktop overlay feedback during actual meetings, VirtualSpeech is the only major option with VR audience simulation, and Oratori focuses on thirty-second drills for a specific upcoming moment like an interview or pitch. Almost everyone in this space is optimizing delivery mechanics — filler words, pace, tone, energy. 
